COVID19 ICD10PCS Value Set for Administration of Immunosuppressive Therapy

This value set includes codes from the following code systems:

  • Include these codes as defined in http://www.icd10data.com/icd10pcs
    Code Display
    3E030WL Introduction of Immunosuppressive into Peripheral Vein, Open
    3E033WL Introduction of Immunosuppressive into Peripheral Vein, Percutaneous
    3E040WL Introduction of Immunosuppressive into Central Vein, Open
    3E043WL Introduction of Immunosuppressive into Central Vein, Percutaneous
    3E050WL Introduction of Immunosuppressive into Peripheral Artery, Open
    3E053WL Introduction of Immunosuppressive into Peripheral Artery, Percutaneous
    3E060WL Introduction of Immunosuppressive into Central Artery, Open
    3E063WL Introduction of Immunosuppressive into Central Artery, Percutaneous
    XW03351 Introduction of Blinatumomab Antineoplastic Immunotherapy into Peripheral Vein, Percutaneous Approach, New Technology Group 1
    XW04351 Introduction of Blinatumomab Antineoplastic Immunotherapy into Central Vein, Percutaneous Approach, New Technology Group 1
